body: Hey buddy, this means its not finding any pictures to load. You might need to make sure its looking in the right directory, and that there are only image files in the directory.

@glenn-jocher  Thanks. I solved it. Actually, the code uses the following:
```
self.shuffled_vector = np.random.choice(self.mat['image_numbers'].ravel(), self.nF,
                                                p=self.mat['image_weights'].ravel())
```
It always generates a list of 847 images in the dataset and related probability for p.  I was using a subset of the 847 images. The code was still producing the list of 847 images which naturally calling some files which were in the subset and causing the above error.

Now, if I use the subset, do I have to produce "targets_c60.mat" file again? My understanding is Yes. But I would like to hear your comments on this.

No, it should be fine. The mat file contains the targets for each image. For example if image 10 is loaded the targets for it can be found in the mat file. If images are missing their targets simply won't be pulled from the loaded mat file.

> I am getting the following error:
> 
> ```
> Traceback (most recent call last):

>     img_all = np.stack(img_all)[:, :, :, ::-1].transpose(0, 3, 1, 2)  # BGR to RGB and cv2 to pytorch
>   File "/sdcc/u/amalik/.local/lib/python3.5/site-packages/numpy/core/shape_base.py", line 349, in stack
>     raise ValueError('need at least one array to stack')
> ValueError: need at least one array to stack
> ```
> I am using 31 images for training. in datasets.py, the img_all array becomes empty.

how have you solved it?

@byiringiro88 As I mentioned:

```
self.shuffled_vector = np.random.choice(self.mat['image_numbers'].ravel(), self.nF,
                                                p=self.mat['image_weights'].ravel())
```
self.mat['image_numbers']  generates a list of 847 images in the dataset and its related 847 probabilities for p. If you are using a subset of the 847 images, the code still produces the list of 847 images. However, you need only 31 images (self.nf). The randomly produced list of 31 images might not contain the images included in your subset.  You need to ensure that the randomly produce list contains all the images that you are using in your subset.
